letter-spacing:-0.15pt">re</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">-</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">found</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> the United Kingdom on the dual principles of Union and Devolution</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:95%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">*It continues the move</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> away from the current</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> grossly overcentralised </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">Whitehall </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">system that devolves </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">only </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">as an expedient and towards a </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">defined settled Federal constitution.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:95%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">*</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">The c</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">oncept of income tax assignment to the nations of the Union is fundamental to this evolution.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:95%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">*</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">Hence w</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">hile</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> the Bill technically only</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> applies to Wales it has important consequences and implications for the Union and </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">its </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">other constituent parts.</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt; line-height:95%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">I also commend the use of</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> pre-legislative scrutiny</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">which </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">will enable</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> these broader implications </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">above </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">to be openly explored and </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">fully </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">debated</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> in Wales and beyond</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">.  As the Political and Constitutional Reform Committee, which I chair, noted in its recent reports on </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">Ensuring Standards in the Quality of Legislation </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">Revisiting Rebuilding the House: the impact of the Wright reforms, </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">pre-legislative scrutiny is a vital way of </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">helping to make</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> legislation</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> workable and comprehensible</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt; line-height:95%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">I particularly welcome the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">financial </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">provisions in Part</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> 2 of the draft Bill</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">I regarded the proposals made by the Silk Commission for the devolution of a package of financial powers to Wales as hugely encouraging.  </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">As the Secretary of State for Wales notes in his foreword, the draft Bill “implements almost all of the recommendations from the Silk Commission’s first report on the devolution of tax and borrowing powers to the National Assembly for Wales and the Welsh Government.”  </span></li><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt; line-height:95%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">The Political and Constitutional Reform Committee has recently </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">published two reports related to</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> devolution:  </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">Prospects for codifying the relationship between central and local government</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">Do we need a constitutional convention for the UK?</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">. The first report argued that</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> the Government should seriously consider the idea of local authorities in England receiving a share of the income tax take for England.  It examined the precedent set by the Scotland Act 2012, which gives the Scottish Pa</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">rliament the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">power to retain 10p rate of</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> income tax for Scottish taxpayers, and will come into force from April 2016.  It also examined</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> the Silk Commission’s proposal for a new Welsh </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">retained </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">rate of income tax.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">   As part of the inquiry that formed the basis of the second report, </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">PCR</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">C</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">heard oral evidence from Paul Silk and Professor Noel Lloyd on the Silk Commission’s recommendations. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt; line-height:95%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">I believe that it is right that </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">England should follow </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">the people of</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> Scotland, and now Wales and</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> have the opportunity to enjoy </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">greater financial devolution</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">Devolved power in many countries has, as the Committee’s local government report noted, been given financial life by the retention of an agreed element of income tax.  </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">Whitehall does not always know best.  Many decisions are best taken at a</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> devolved</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> level.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">It is hugely encouraging that the devolv</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">ed parts of the Union have the opportunity to take</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> responsibility for </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">some of </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">their ow</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">n budgets.  The Committee worked through </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> in </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">its local government report how</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">Westminster </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">Government</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> could implement</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> such a relationship for England too.  </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">Devolution should be regarded as a principle, not a political expedient</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">, and should apply to England, as well as to Wales, Scotland and Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">It is important for England and the other nations of the Union that the Wales Bill makes progress and is not delayed by the desire for perfection.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:95%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt; text-decoration:underline">Financial powers</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt; line-height:95%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">The UK Government currently </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">funds</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> most of the budget of </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">the devolved administration in Wales</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">.  The Welsh Government has relied on the block grant funding since 1999</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">Despite the spe</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">nding discretion enjoyed by </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">the Welsh Government</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">, it</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> does not have the ability to change the size of its budget, as it does not have tax powers, other than local taxation.    When compared to the other devolved nations around the world, Wales is unusual in that it has legislative spending powers, but not taxing abilities.  The Silk Commission noted that this was problematic because “the Welsh Government and the National Assembly for Wales are not accountable to the Welsh electorate for how revenue is raised in the same way that they are for how it is spent.”  This is an anomal</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">y that the draft Bill would begin</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> to redress.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">The long journey from block grant funding to a mixed </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">assigned </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">income tax /block </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">grant model is about to begin.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">here are many obst</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">cles and difficulties along the way but it is now a matter of when</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">not if</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> the goal of financial devolution for Wales and the other nations of the Union can be achieved</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">This new settlement once fully evolved will last for the foreseeable future.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt; line-height:95%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">The Silk Commission outlined several principles against which changes in the funding system for Wales should be judged.  It stated that specific attention should be given to accountability, empowerment,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> efficiency, economic incentivi</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">ation and equality.  In order to provide fuller financial accountability the Commission made a number of specific recommendations.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt; line-height:95%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">The current block grant system leaves the Welsh Government unaccountable for the revenue raised to support it.  As such, the Silk Commission recommended that some taxes be devolved and brought under the prevue of the Welsh Government.  The report stated: “there is a range of smaller taxes that, if devolved, </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">while only going a limited way to increasing financial accountability would better empower the National Assembly for Wales to deliver policy objectives in devolved areas.”  As such, the report recommended that the following taxes be devolved: Stamp Duty Land Tax, landfill tax, the aggregates levy, and long haul rates of Air Passenger Duty (with future consideration of full devolution of Air Passenger Duty).  It is also recommended that business rates be fully devolved in the same way as in Scotland and Northern Ireland. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">The draft Bill devolves Stamp Duty Land Tax and landfill tax to Wales, which will enable these taxes to be set at an appropriate level to meet Wales’s needs.  </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">The draft Bill also </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">follows</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> the Commi</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">ssion’s recommendation to </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">devolve</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> fully business rates</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">It is disappointing</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">, however,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> that the draft Bill does not devolve long haul rates of Air Passenger Duty.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt; line-height:95%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">The progress on devolving smaller taxes to Wales and other nations of the Union is very welcome.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">However it is the evolution of Income Tax which is  central to the development of </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">the principles of Union and D</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">evolution.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; letter-spacing:-0.15pt">Here t</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size